    "updated_at": "2014-01-17T22:10:33Z",
    "body": "That said, I think we should revisit these categorizations before 1.0, with an eye towards possible future data parallelism. Atomic is quite different from Cell in that, while it permits mutation and hence is not freezable, it's also threadsafe. \n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
