    "body": "I've started looking into changing atomics to use immutable references. There's one snag though in that `drop` creates aliased `&mut` pointers, as in \n\n```\n#[unsafe_destructor]\nimpl<T> Drop for AtomicOption<T> {\n    fn drop(&mut self) {\n        let _ = self.take(SeqCst);\n    }\n}\n```\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
